-- Mitchell Communications Chairman May Accept Aegis Board Seat if Offered
-- Rebecca Keenan
-- 2010-08-01T00:31:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/mitchell-communications-chairman-may-accept-aegis-board-seat-if-offered.html

          
          
             Mitchell Communications Group Ltd.’s
Chairman Harold Mitchell said he would accept a board position
with his company’s suitor Aegis Group Plc. if it was offered.  
 “If asked, I’d happily do it,” Mitchell said in an
interview on Australian Broadcasting Corp.’s Inside Business
program.   
 Aegis last week agreed to buy Mitchell to gain the top
position in the Australian market. The offer was worth A$363
million when it was announced on July 29.   
